Text:
If you want a TI emulator, just go here
http://www.ticalc.org/archives/files/fileinfo/84/8442.html
and download that, you will need a file from TI's actual website too to run it, you can find that here
http://education.ti.com/educationportal/sites/US/productDetail/us_ti89.html?bid=8

that program will emulate any TI calc, no need to torrent

dorun:
As far as I know you are wrong.  Virtual TI (vti) requires a ROM image (.rom file), which is not the same as a calculator operating system (.89u for example, which you linked to).  I am not able to import a .89u file, nor does the import work when I alter the file extensions.

~fogus
